    <li class="standard" id="comment-5197">
      <div class="commentname">
        Kevin        on
        August 6th, 2009              </div>
      <div class='commenttext'>
        <div class="commentp">
          	      		          	<p>Regarding #42, boiled water freezes faster: </p>
<p>One of the things that causes freezer burn is temperature fluctuations in the freezer. To avoid freezer burn, you want to keep the temperature in the freezer as constant as possible.</p>
<p>Putting an ice cube tray of hot water into the freezer will cause the exact kind of temp fluctuation that contributes to freezer burn. </p>
<p>So you have to ask yourself; is throwing out meat that should otherwise still be good a price you&#8217;re willing to pay to get your ice cubes 5 minutes sooner?</p>
